stories.description:
In App.tsx, the NotificationData union type has a catch-all `| { type: string }` member that makes the entire type equivalent to `{ type: string; groupId?: string }`, defeating type safety.

Remove the catch-all and add an explicit fallback type for unknown notification types:
```ts
type NotificationData =
  | { type: 'group_message'; groupId: string }
  | { type: 'friend_request' }
  | { type: 'notification' }
  | { type: string; [key: string]: unknown };  // structured catch-all
```

Actually, the cleanest fix is to just remove `| { type: string }` entirely and ensure the switch/if-else in handleNotificationTap has an exhaustive else clause (which it already does — the else navigates to Profile/Notifications). All incoming notification types that aren't explicitly handled fall into the else branch.
